generated_description:
The Experience

Standing at 4050 feet, South Crocker Mountain is a standout peak in Maine. Known for its rugged and challenging terrain, it offers a quintessential hiking experience.

The Challenge

Hikers often choose the **Crocker Cirque Loop**, a **11.5 mile** route gaining significant elevation. As part of the **Maine 4000-Footers**, it draws peak-baggers from across the region.

Peak Bagging Logic

**Peak Bagging Opportunity:** Consider connecting this hike with **North Crocker Mountain**, which is just 1.4 miles away. Linking these peaks is a popular way to maximize your day on the trail.
